Date: 28/10/1843
Source: Daily Southern Cross
Author:
Vol / Page: 4
Edition:
Quote: Volcanic land.   This is situated adjacent to or around the bases of the volcanic hills, and is too much encumbered with scoria for general cultivation, and the expence [sic] of clearing it must depend entirely on that particular, the stones however may be employed in making durable fences, if however completely cleared it is light and rich, and well suited for gardens and vineyards.
